{"type":"message","id":"243edee8","parentId":"564b539a","timestamp":"2026-06-03T02:51:35.706Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_f45az45u8rl9_2","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"- Fetching skill\nauto-updater  Auto-Updater Skill\nSummary: Automatically update Clawdbot and all installed skills once daily. Runs via cron, checks for updates, applies them, and messages the user with a summary of what changed.\nOwner: maximeprades\nCreated: 2026-01-13T16:58:59.453Z\nUpdated: 2026-05-18T22:54:14.317Z\nLatest: 1.0.0\nLicense: MIT-0 (Free to use, modify, and redistribute. No attribution required.)\nTags: latest=1.0.0"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":3218,"aggregated":"- Fetching skill\nauto-updater  Auto-Updater Skill\nSummary: Automatically update Clawdbot and all installed skills once daily. Runs via cron, checks for updates, applies them, and messages the user with a summary of what changed.\nOwner: maximeprades\nCreated: 2026-01-13T16:58:59.453Z\nUpdated: 2026-05-18T22:54:14.317Z\nLatest: 1.0.0\nLicense: MIT-0 (Free to use, modify, and redistribute. No attribution required.)\nTags: latest=1.0.0","cwd":"/home/halei/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1780455095704}}
{"type":"message","id":"f3349e9f","parentId":"243edee8","timestamp":"2026-06-03T02:51:44.450Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"升级报错：\"local changes (no match)\"——说明我们装的这版 SKILL.md **有本地改动**（很可能是我之前把它的路径 `.learnings/` 改成了 `memory/learnings/`）。我得先看本地和远端的 diff，然后决定是 `--force` 覆盖还是保留本地修改。\n\n我得先确认本地改了什么，避免升级把我针对路径做的适配给冲掉："},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_3gyl98q3dhtr_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd /home/halei/.openclaw/workspace/skills/self-improving-agent && diff <(cat SKILL.md) <(clawhub inspect self-improving-agent 2>&1 | sed -n '/^---$/,/^$/p' | tail -n +2 | head -n -1) 2>&1 | head -20"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_3gyl98q3dhtr_2","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd /home/halei/.openclaw/workspace/skills/self-improving-agent && ls .clawhub/ 2>&1; echo \"---\"; cat .clawhub/*.json 2>&1 2>/dev/null | head -30"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax(49套餐)","model":"MiniMax-M3","usage":{"input":190,"output":251,"cacheRead":71229,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":71670,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1780455095861,"responseId":"066ec9b87698c17ece3ba86de603339c"}}
{"type":"message","id":"2202bb84","parentId":"f3349e9f","timestamp":"2026-06-03T02:51:47.040Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_3gyl98q3dhtr_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"1,644d0\n< ---\n< name: self-improvement\n< description: \"Captures learnings, errors, and corrections to enable continuous improvement. Use when: (1) A command or operation fails unexpectedly, (2) User corrects Claude ('No, that's wrong...', 'Actually...'), (3) User requests a capability that doesn't exist, (4) An external API or tool fails, (5) Claude realizes its knowledge is outdated or incorrect, (6) A better approach is discovered for a recurring task. Also review learnings before major tasks.\"\n< metadata:\n< ---\n< \n< # Self-Improvement Skill\n< \n< Log learnings and errors to markdown files for continuous improvement. Coding agents can later process these into fixes, and important learnings get promoted to project memory.\n< \n< ## First-Use Initialisation\n< \n< Before logging anything, ensure the `.learnings/` directory and files exist in the project or workspace root. If any are missing, create them:\n< \n< ```bash\n< mkdir -p .learnings\n< [ -f .learnings/LEARNINGS.md ] || printf \"# Learnings\\n\\nCorrections, insights, and knowledge gaps captured during development.\\n\\n**Categories**: correction | insight | knowledge_gap | best_practice\\n\\n---\\n\" > .learnings/LEARNINGS.md\n< [ -f .learnings/ERRORS.md ] || printf \"# Errors\\n\\nCommand failures and integration errors.\\n\\n---\\n\" > .learnings/ERRORS.md\n< [ -f .learnings/FEATURE_REQUESTS.md ] || printf \"# Feature Requests\\n\\nCapabilities requested by the user.\\n\\n---\\n\" > .learnings/FEATURE_REQUESTS.md"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":2483,"aggregated":"1,644d0\n< ---\n< name: self-improvement\n< description: \"Captures learnings, errors, and corrections to enable continuous improvement. Use when: (1) A command or operation fails unexpectedly, (2) User corrects Claude ('No, that's wrong...', 'Actually...'), (3) User requests a capability that doesn't exist, (4) An external API or tool fails, (5) Claude realizes its knowledge is outdated or incorrect, (6) A better approach is discovered for a recurring task. Also review learnings before major tasks.\"\n< metadata:\n< ---\n< \n< # Self-Improvement Skill\n< \n< Log learnings and errors to markdown files for continuous improvement. Coding agents can later process these into fixes, and important learnings get promoted to project memory.\n< \n< ## First-Use Initialisation\n< \n< Before logging anything, ensure the `.learnings/` directory and files exist in the project or workspace root. If any are missing, create them:\n< \n< ```bash\n< mkdir -p .learnings\n< [ -f .learnings/LEARNINGS.md ] || printf \"# Learnings\\n\\nCorrections, insights, and knowledge gaps captured during development.\\n\\n**Categories**: correction | insight | knowledge_gap | best_practice\\n\\n---\\n\" > .learnings/LEARNINGS.md\n< [ -f .learnings/ERRORS.md ] || printf \"# Errors\\n\\nCommand failures and integration errors.\\n\\n---\\n\" > .learnings/ERRORS.md\n< [ -f .learnings/FEATURE_REQUESTS.md ] || printf \"# Feature Requests\\n\\nCapabilities requested by the user.\\n\\n---\\n\" > .learnings/FEATURE_REQUESTS.md","cwd":"/home/halei/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1780455107037}}
